---
import Base from "../layouts/base.astro";
---

<Base
  title="Why Discovery-as-a-Service Works"
  description="What makes us different to consultancies and contractors"
  type="WebPage"
  canonicalURL="https://getclarity.win/why-clarity-works"
>
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 py-20 text-center">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-12">Why Discovery-as-a-Service Works</h1>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 1: The Problem -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 px-4 mb-20">
    <div class="text-left">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">When you're moving fast…</h2>
      <p class="text-lg">
        It's hard to pause and think clearly. Priorities multiply. Context
        shifts. And every decision feels like a gamble.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="text-left">
      <ul class="list-disc list-outside pl-5 space-y-3 text-lg">
        <li>Your calendar is full, but progress is slow.</li>
        <li>Your team wants direction but you're stuck between priorities.</li>
        <li>
          You've started projects just to get answers and now they've spiralled.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 2: Why Existing Solutions Fail -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 mb-20 text-left text-lg">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Traditional help comes too late</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">
      Traditional help arrives too late. Clarity. is your shortcut to
      experienced thinking. No waiting, no hiring, no heavy onboarding. We stack
      speed, flexibility, and outcome clarity into a model that meets you where
      the real pressure lives.
    </p>
    <p>
      Clarity. fits the moment. No long contract negotiation, no statement of
      work. Just experienced thinking when the pressure's on.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 3: What Makes Clarity. Different -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 mb-20 text-left">
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Why Clarity. works</h2>
        <p class="text-lg mb-4">
          We fit into your world, not the other way around. No decks. No drama.
          No drawn-out discovery.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg">
          We give you insight that's fast, focused, and informed — so you can
          act with confidence, not hesitation.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-6 rounded-xl bg-[#A7D5F2] dark:bg-[#5AA6D6]">
        <p class="font-semibold mb-2 text-center">You get:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-outside pl-5 text-left text-base space-y-2">
          <li>Strategic decisions backed by senior expertise</li>
          <li>Less rework, more momentum</li>
          <li>A flexible partner you don't have to manage</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 4: Action vs Inaction Framing -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 mb-20">
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
      <div
        class="p-6 rounded-xl bg-[#75C1E8] dark:bg-[#429EDB] text-left text-white"
      >
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">When you act:</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-outside pl-5 text-base space-y-2">
          <li>Things move faster and stay on track</li>
          <li>You regain control of your priorities</li>
          <li>Others align faster, because your direction is clear</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div
        class="p-6 rounded-xl bg-[#808080]/10 dark:bg-[#666666]/30 text-left"
      >
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">When you don't:</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-outside pl-5 text-base space-y-2">
          <li>Decisions get delayed and diluted</li>
          <li>Your team fills the gaps their own way</li>
          <li>Opportunity windows quietly close</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section 5: Closing -->
  <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-10 text-center">
    <p class="text-xl font-medium mb-6">
      Clarity. works because it gives you experienced thinking. Just enough,
      just in time.
    </p>
    <p class="text-lg mb-8">
      You don't need a project to make progress. With Clarity., you get the
      insight and confidence to move forward. Fast. Just enough, just in time,
      just for you.
    </p>

    <!-- <a
      href="/support-plans-preview-93xz4/"
      class="inline-block px-6 py-3 rounded-xl bg-[#429EDB] text-white font-semibold hover:bg-[#1F78C1] transition"
    >
      Explore Support Plans
    </a> -->
  </section>

  <!-- Navigation Arrows -->
  <section class="my-16 flex flex-col items-center gap-4 text-center">
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
      Want to know what you get with our support plans? Check out our 30/60/90.
    </p>
    <div class="flex gap-12 justify-center items-center">
      <!-- Left Arrow Link -->
      <a
        href="/"
        aria-label="Previous page"
        class="hover:text-blue-600 transition"
      >
        <svg
          xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
          fill="none"
          stroke="currentColor"
          stroke-width="2"
          viewBox="0 0 24 24"
          width="64"
          height="64"
        >
          <path
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
            d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7"></path>
        </svg>
      </a>

      <!-- Right Arrow Link -->
      <a
        href="/what-you-get/"
        aria-label="Next page"
        class="hover:text-blue-600 transition"
      >
        <svg
          xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
          fill="none"
          stroke="currentColor"
          stroke-width="2"
          viewBox="0 0 24 24"
          width="64"
          height="64"
        >
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7"
          ></path>
        </svg>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="text-center mb-24">
    <p class="text-lg mb-4">Ready?</p>
    <a
      href="/"
      class="inline-block bg-[#429EDB] text-white font-semibold px-6 py-3 rounded hover:bg-[#1F78C1] transition"
    >
      Join the Waitlist
    </a>
  </div>
</Base>
